      "type": "edit",
      "id": "6cb19a62f3cf89d2",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "6cb19a62f3cf89d2",
        "text": "# The classical right of neutrality\nIn initial assessments, the arms deliveries were seen as a violation of the law of neutrality, which, however, did not make Germany a party to the war.1) The law of neutrality regulates the relationship between states fighting in an international armed conflict (belligerents) and states not participating in the conflict (neutrals)."
