        "id": "71880d478a168ef2",
        "text": "This design flaw was also evident in the case of Russia's attack on Ukraine. On February 25, 2022, Russia vetoed a resolution supported by 82 states in which the Security Council would have \"strongly deplored the aggression of the Russian Federation against Ukraine in violation of Article 2(4) of the Charter of the United Nations\" and called on Russia to immediately cease fire and withdraw from Ukraine. In the absence of action by the Security Council, commentators in Germany therefore assumed the application of the law of neutrality and its violation by the arms deliveries to Ukraine.3)"
