      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "471d295ea1481796",
        "text": "Of the 193 member states of the United Nations, 141 voted in favor of the resolution, 35 abstained, and only five (Russia, Belarus, North Korea, Eritrea, and Syria) voted against. Unlike the Security Council, the General Assembly cannot make a legally binding determination of aggressor, but its resolutions are widely viewed as expressing the views of world opinion. In the international law literature, a two-thirds majority in the Genreal Assembly has been considered sufficient to put the individual determination of aggressor by individual states beyond doubt as to their bona fides. With 141 votes in favor of the resolution, this criterion is more than met."
